BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 190.8 720 Td (Chapter 1: Louis Braille) Tj ET
BT 0.4 g /F4 12 Tf 190.8 698 Td (Age 15 - Invented Braille Reading System) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 688 m 540 688 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 660 Td (Louis Braille lost his sight in an accident when he was only 3 years old.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 644 Td (In 1800s France, blind people had almost no way to read or write.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 628 Td (At school for the blind, Louis was frustrated. The raised-letter books were clumsy.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 612 Td (At age 15, he invented a system of raised dots that could represent any letter!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 596 Td (Using just 6 dots in different patterns, he created an entire alphabet for the blind.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 580 Td (Today, millions of blind people worldwide read using Braille's brilliant system.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 544 Td (THE SCIENCE: HOW TOUCH AND NERVES WORK) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 524 Td (Your fingertips have about 3,000 touch receptors per square centimeter!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 508 Td (These receptors detect pressure, vibration, and texture with incredible sensitivity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 492 Td (Nerve signals from your fingertips travel to your brain at up to 250 mph!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 476 Td (Your brain can distinguish bumps as small as 0.04mm - smaller than a grain of sand!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 460 Td (Blind people often develop even more sensitive touch as their brain adapts.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 370 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 429 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 409 Td (* Braille uses patterns of 1-6 raised dots that represent letters, numbers, and punctuation.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 391 Td (* Experienced Braille readers can read up to 200 words per minute by touch!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 373 Td (* Braille is used in over 130 languages worldwide today.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 340 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 324 Td (Close your eyes and try to identify 5 objects by touch alone. How sensitive are your fingers?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 304 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 288 Td (How does losing one sense \(like sight\) make other senses \(like touch\) stronger?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
