BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 176.4 720 Td (Chapter 2: Philo Farnsworth) Tj ET
BT 0.4 g /F4 12 Tf 185.04000000000002 698 Td (Age 14 - Conceived the Idea for Television) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 688 m 540 688 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 660 Td (In 1920, 14-year-old Philo was plowing a potato field in Idaho.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 644 Td (Looking at the parallel rows of soil, he had a brilliant idea!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 628 Td ('What if you could capture an image line by line, like rows in a field?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 612 Td (He sketched his idea for his high school teacher: electronic television!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 596 Td (By age 21, he built the first fully electronic TV and transmitted an image.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 580 Td (His idea from a potato field changed how the entire world receives information!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 544 Td (THE SCIENCE: HOW SCREENS CREATE IMAGES) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 524 Td (TV screens create images using thousands of tiny pixels \(picture elements\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 508 Td (Each pixel produces light in combinations of red, green, and blue \(RGB\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 492 Td (By mixing different amounts of these three colors, ANY color can be created!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 476 Td (Your screen refreshes 30-60 times per second - too fast for your eyes to notice!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 460 Td (Farnsworth's original idea used an electron beam scanning line by line \(CRT technology\).) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 370 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 429 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 409 Td (* A 4K TV has over 8 million pixels, each with 3 sub-pixels \(24+ million tiny lights!\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 391 Td (* Farnsworth first demonstrated TV at age 21 with a simple straight line image.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 373 Td (* He said he hoped TV would be used for education - 'There is nothing worthwhile on it.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 340 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 324 Td (Look at a screen with a magnifying glass. Can you see the tiny red, green, and blue sub-pixels?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 304 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 288 Td (How did looking at rows in a potato field inspire the biggest invention of the century?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
