BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 186.0 720 Td (Chapter 3: Frank Epperson) Tj ET
BT 0.4 g /F4 12 Tf 182.16000000000003 698 Td (Age 11 - Accidentally Invented the Popsicle) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 688 m 540 688 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 660 Td (In 1905, 11-year-old Frank was mixing powdered soda and water on his porch.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 644 Td (He accidentally left the cup outside overnight with the mixing stick still in it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 628 Td (That night, the temperature dropped below freezing in San Francisco.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 612 Td (The next morning, Frank found his drink frozen solid around the stick!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 596 Td (He pulled it out and had the world's first popsicle! He called it the 'Epsicle.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 580 Td (Years later, he patented it and sold millions. All from a happy accident!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 544 Td (THE SCIENCE: FREEZING AND SOLUTIONS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 524 Td (Pure water freezes at 32F \(0C\), but dissolved substances lower the freezing point!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 508 Td (That is why Frank's sugary soda water froze at a lower temperature than plain water.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 492 Td (This is called 'freezing point depression' - salt on icy roads uses the same principle!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 476 Td (When water freezes, molecules slow down and form a crystal structure \(ice\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 460 Td (Adding sugar or salt disrupts crystal formation, requiring colder temperatures to freeze.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 370 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 429 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 409 Td (* Americans eat over 2 billion popsicles every year!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 391 Td (* Ocean water freezes at about 28.4F \(-2C\) because of dissolved salt.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 373 Td (* Ice cream trucks exist because Frank's 'accident' created a whole new industry!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 340 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 324 Td (Make popsicles! Freeze juice in cups with sticks. Try salt water vs sugar water - which freezes first?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 304 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 288 Td (Many great inventions were accidents. Why is being observant so important for scientists?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
