BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 195.60000000000002 720 Td (Chapter 6: Jack Andraka) Tj ET
BT 0.4 g /F4 12 Tf 187.92000000000002 698 Td (Age 15 - Developed a Low-Cost Cancer Test) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 688 m 540 688 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 660 Td (When a close family friend died of pancreatic cancer, 15-year-old Jack was devastated.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 644 Td (He learned that the existing test was 60 years old, expensive, and missed 70% of cases!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 628 Td ('I can do better,' he decided. He spent months researching at the library and online.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 612 Td (He developed a paper sensor that detects a cancer protein 168 times faster!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 596 Td (His test costs just 3 cents \(vs $800!\) and takes 5 minutes \(vs hours!\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 580 Td (After being rejected by 197 labs, one professor said yes - and Jack proved it worked!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 544 Td (THE SCIENCE: BIOSENSORS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 524 Td (Biosensors detect biological substances \(proteins, DNA\) using chemical reactions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 508 Td (Jack's sensor uses antibodies that bind specifically to a cancer protein \(mesothelin\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 492 Td (When the protein attaches to antibodies on the paper, electrical properties change.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 476 Td (Carbon nanotubes on filter paper create a network that responds to the protein binding.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 460 Td (This is similar to how COVID rapid tests work - antibodies detecting specific targets!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 370 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 429 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 409 Td (* Jack was rejected by 197 researchers before finding one who believed in his idea!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 391 Td (* His test is 26,000 times less expensive and 400 times more sensitive than existing tests.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 373 Td (* Persistence paid off - he never gave up despite nearly 200 rejections!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 340 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 324 Td (Research 'antibodies' - how do they recognize specific things? Draw how a lock-and-key system works.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 304 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 288 Td (Jack was rejected 197 times before succeeding. What does this teach about persistence?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
