BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 205.2 720 Td (Chapter 7: Kelvin Doe) Tj ET
BT 0.4 g /F4 12 Tf 170.64000000000001 698 Td (Age 13 - Built Batteries and a Radio from Trash) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 688 m 540 688 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 660 Td (In Sierra Leone, Africa, 13-year-old Kelvin had no access to electronics or electricity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 644 Td (But he was endlessly curious and loved taking things apart to see how they worked.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 628 Td (He collected discarded electronics and scrap metal from trash dumps.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 612 Td (From this 'junk,' he built batteries, a generator, and eventually a radio station!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 596 Td (His community radio station broadcast music and news to his whole neighborhood.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 580 Td (He became the youngest person ever invited to MIT's 'Visiting Practitioner' program!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 544 Td (THE SCIENCE: BATTERIES FROM RECYCLED MATERIALS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 524 Td (Kelvin made batteries by combining acid, soda, and metal from recycled electronics.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 508 Td (A battery needs two different metals and an electrolyte \(acid/base solution\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 492 Td (Chemical reactions between the metals and electrolyte produce an electrical current.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 476 Td (His generator used a motor in reverse: spinning it by hand produced electricity!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 460 Td (Radio transmitters convert electrical signals into electromagnetic waves.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 370 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 429 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 409 Td (* Kelvin had no formal engineering training - he taught himself from discarded textbooks!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 391 Td (* He created his own radio station: 'DJ Focus' broadcasting to his community.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 373 Td (* He later started a company to bring power to communities without electricity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 340 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 324 Td (Build a simple battery: put copper and zinc strips in lemon juice. Measure voltage with a multimeter!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 304 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 288 Td (How does Kelvin's story show that creativity is more important than resources?) Tj ET

endstream
