BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 205.2 720 Td (Chapter 8: YOUR Turn!) Tj ET
BT 0.4 g /F4 12 Tf 199.44 698 Td (The Next Great Inventor Could Be YOU!) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 688 m 540 688 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 660 Td (Every inventor in this book was once just a kid with a question or a problem.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 644 Td (They did not have special powers or expensive labs. They had CURIOSITY and PERSISTENCE.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 628 Td (Louis was blind. Kelvin had no electricity. Jack was rejected 197 times.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 612 Td (But they all shared one thing: they saw a problem and decided to solve it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 596 Td (The world has millions of problems still waiting for creative solutions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 580 Td (And the next great inventor might be reading this book right now. That means YOU!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 544 Td (THE SCIENCE: THE SCIENTIFIC METHOD) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 524 Td (Step 1: OBSERVE - Notice a problem that needs solving.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 508 Td (Step 2: QUESTION - Ask 'Why does this happen?' or 'How can I fix this?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 492 Td (Step 3: RESEARCH - Learn everything you can about the problem.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 476 Td (Step 4: HYPOTHESIZE - Make an educated guess about a solution.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 460 Td (Step 5: EXPERIMENT - Build a prototype and test your idea.) Tj ET
